[2] Viet Nam
Date: Mon 7 Jun 2010
Source: Radio The Voice of Viet Nam (VOV) News [edited]
<http://english.vovnews.vn/Home/More-cases-of-dengue-fever-reported-in-HCM-City/20106/116265.vov>


More cases of dengue fever reported in Ho Chi Minh City
-------------------------------------------------------
The number of dengue fever patients is rising in Ho Chi Minh City due to
unexpected rains in some districts of the city. Currently, around 65 cases
of dengue fever are being detected in the city every week, up 20 per cent
against last week [week of 1 Jun 2010]. In the next few months, the number
of cases is expected to continue to rise in Thu Duc, Tan Phu, Binh Tan, and
Binh Chanh [districts].

The city's health department has advised on drastic measures to prevent
dengue fever in the rainy season and has asked that all localities and
medical centres work together, clean up the environment, and eradicate
mosquito larvae. The city's Children Hospital No 1 has treated 57 cases of
dengue fever as of 4 Jun 2010.

--
communicated by:
PRO/MBDS
<promed-mbds@promedmail.org>

[The newswire above reports the increase of DF/DHF cases in Ho Chi Minh
City. Increases of DF/DHF cases were also reported in An Giang, Da Nang,
and Ha Noi in the early months of 2010 (see prior PRO/MBDS postings listed
below).

However, in its report of 20 May 2010 (available in Vietnamese at
<http://www.moh.gov.vn/homebyt/vn/portal/InfoDetail.jsp?area=58&cat=1456&ID=8602>),
the Viet Nam Ministry of Health reported 3388 DF/DHF cases from 40
provinces and cities; among those, 9 died in May 2010. The accumulated
number of DF/DHF in Viet Nam in 2010 is 12 868 cases, of which 12 died.
Compared with the same period in 2009 (16 635 cases and 14 deaths), the
number of DF/DHF cases has decreased by 22.6 per cent and the number of
deaths due to DF/DHF decreases by 2 cases.

According to the WHO's Regional Office for the Western Pacific (WHO/WPRO)
report available at <http://www.wpro.who.int/sites/mvp/data/dengue/>, there
were a total of 105 370 cases and 87 deaths of DF/DHF reported in Viet Nam
during 2009.

For a map of Viet Nam with provinces, see
<http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f0/VietnameseProvincesMap.png>.
The interactive HealthMap/ProMED-mail map with direct links to other
outbreaks in Viet Nam and surrounding countries reported on ProMED-mail and
PRO/MBDS can be accessed at <http://healthmap.org/r/008O>. - Mod.QCN]

