[6] Mayotte
Date: Mon 31 May 2010
Source: Mayotte.com [in French, trans. Corr. SB, edited]
<http://www.mayottehebdo.com/content/view/2476/47/>


As part of the epidemiological surveillance set up in Mayotte, new cases of
dengue have been identified. The epidemiological assessment has risen from
26 cases to 32 confirmed cases (including 11 locally acquired cases), 19
probable cases (including 16 locally acquired cases). Confirmed cases are
spread throughout the island and no severe form [of the infection] has been
identified.

The downward trend of the circulation of dengue virus in Mayotte observed
in the previous week [week of 23 May] has not been confirmed. The
identification of confirmed cases indicates a local source. The number of
confirmed cases of dengue on the island remains weak, without detection in
households. In case of any sudden onset of fever associated with headache,
muscle pain, rash, nausea, vomiting, bleeding or fatigue, see a doctor.

--
communicated by:
HealthMap Alerts vis ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[A 5 May 2010 report indicated that dengue virus 3 is the virus circulating
on Mayotte (see ProMED archive no. 20100517.1620).

