[9] Brazil (Sao Paulo)
Date: Sat 12 Jun 2010
Source: Estadao.com.br [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.estadao.com.br/noticias/vidae,mesmo-com-queda-de-80-epidemia-de-dengue-em-sp-e-a-pior-da-historia,565703,0.htm>


The dengue epidemic in Sao Paulo state is now the worst in its history,
pointed out by a survey of the Secretariat of Health, despite that the
number of cases in May 2010 is 80 per cent lower than in the previous
month. The totals from the state Secretariat of Health reported on the
evening of last Friday [11 Jun 2010] reported a total of 121 270 cases of
the disease were notified in 2010, compared with 92 345 [dengue cases] that
occurred in 2007, until then, the worst epidemic year.

The 98 deaths this year [2010] are also an historical record as already
pointed out by the office in early May. The survey showed that 78.6 per
cent of the infections were concentrated in 50 cities in all of Sao Paulo.
The peak of cases occurred in March this year, with 44 920 infections.

Of the total of 121 270 confirmed [dengue] cases between January and May
this year [2010], 22 710 were registered in the city of Ribeirao Preto and
another 11 185 in Sao Jose do Rio Preto. Guaruja had 8048 occurrences and
Santos 7860.

The secretariat attributed the increase reaching high prevalence to the
rains, especially in the 1st 3 months of the year, that were propitious for
the proliferation of the dengue mosquito [vector]. However, in 2008 there
was a reduction in preventive action.

[byline: Fabiane Leite]

--
communicated by
HealthMap Alerts via ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The 9 Jun 2010 edition of VNews
(<http://www.vnews.com.br/noticia.php?id=73468>) indicated that in Sao
Sabastiao, Sao Paulo state, the number of new cases fell 80 per cent
between May and June, and the mosquito control actions have not stopped.
These actions involved teachers and students from 4 schools in teaching the
population about elimination of vector mosquito breeding sites.

In Taubate, another city with a dengue epidemic, transmission also
decelerated with colder weather. That municipality registered 4600 reports
of the disease up to now. Another report of 10 Jun 2010 in Gazeta de
Piracicaba (in Portuguese,
<http://www.gazetadepiracicaba.com.br/conteudo/mostra_noticia.asp?noticia=1691403&area=26050&authent=626FBCFAED2403132E8BEEFE554224>
indicated that Piracicaba, Sao Paulo state, had its 1st fatal case of DHF
in May 2010. The municipal Secretariat of Health indicated that Piracicaba
had recorded 1208 dengue cases this year, with 434 cases of classical
dengue, 2 of DHF and one of dengue with complications. An additional 7
cases are under investigation.

A map showing the states in Brazil can be accessed at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/brazil.jpg>. A
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Brazil can be accessed at
<http://healthmap.org/r/008S>. - Mod.TY]
